meanings.definition: To be higher in rank or position than someone else.
meanings.sent1: In the game, Sarah outranked all her friends by winning first place.
meanings.sent2: John outranked his colleagues and became the manager of the team.
meanings.sent3: The cat outranked the dog in the household hierarchy, much to the dog's dismay.
meanings.sent4: Her dedication to her studies outranked any obstacles that came her way.
meanings.sent5: The sun outranked all other stars in the sky with its brightness.

meanings.definition: To surpass in rank or importance.
meanings.sent1: The new movie outranked all others in popularity at the box office.
meanings.sent2: His skills and experience outranked those of his competitors, securing him the job.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outranked the birds in the park when it came to gathering nuts for winter.
meanings.sent4: The student's creativity outranked his peers, earning him praise from the teacher.
meanings.sent5: The mountain peak outranked all others in majesty and grandeur.
